article.description: — Isaiah Miller had 22 points as UNC Greensboro beat Furman 64-58 on Wednesday.
article.headline: Miller scores 22 to lead UNC Greensboro over Furman 64-58
article.linkText: Miller scores 22 to lead UNC Greensboro over Furman 64-58
article.story: GREENSBORO, N.C. -- — Isaiah Miller had 22 points as UNC Greensboro beat Furman 64-58 on Wednesday. Keyshaun Langley had 11 points for UNC Greensboro (14-6, 9-3 Southern Conference), which earned its fourth straight home victory. Clay Mounce had 19 points and 16 rebounds for the Paladins (12-7, 6-4). Mike Bothwell added eight rebounds. The Spartans evened the season series against the Paladins. Furman defeated UNC Greensboro 68-49 on Monday. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
